			<ns0:name>dschuff@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/dschuff@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Today, we are using cygwin to build llvm and binutils for the PNaCl toolchain on Windows. Cygwin is slow and can be unreliable, we should use something else.
The main options are MSVC and mingw. LLVM will build with MSVC, but binutils will probably not. Since we need to use LLVM's gold plugin for LTO, and I'm not sure MSVC and ming are compatible in that way, we may just want to use mingw for both (or even do an MSVC build for clang and a mingw build for the plugin).</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2013-06-06T15:50:55.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2013-06-06T15:50:55.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>New</ns2:status><ns2:state>open</ns2:state><ns0:title>Switch PNaCl Windows toolchain build away from cygwin</ns0:title><ns2:label>Type-Defect</ns2:label><ns2:label>Mstone-30</ns2:label><ns2:label>Pri-2</ns2:label><ns2:label>Component-PNaCl</ns2:label><ns2:label>OS-Windows</ns2:label><ns2:label>Arch-All</ns2:label><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/3473/comments/full" rel="replies" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3473" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/full/3473" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns2:stars>2</ns2:stars><ns2:id>3473</ns2:id></ns0:entry>